    <header>
        <h1>Wazuh Configuration Issues</h1>
    </header>
    <main>
        <h2>Overview</h2>
        <p>I'm currently troubleshooting issues with our Wazuh setup at work. The main challenges revolve around configuration settings, agents not reporting correctly, and inconsistencies in log collection.</p>
        
        <h2>Current Problems</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>Wazuh agents failing to connect or sync with the manager.</li>
            <li>Rules not triggering alerts as expected.</li>
            <li>Unexpected errors in <code>ossec.log</code> during startup.</li>
            <li>Difficulty applying custom configuration changes without breaking existing rules.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Next Steps</h2>
        <p>Plan of action to resolve the issues:</p>
        <ol>
            <li>Review agent and manager connectivity logs.</li>
            <li>Validate configuration syntax using <code>ossec-control</code> tools.</li>
            <li>Test custom rules in a controlled environment before deployment.</li>
            <li>Document all changes for future reference and troubleshooting.</li>
        </ol>

        <p>If anyone has insights or tips on managing Wazuh configurations effectively, feel free to reach out or open an issue on this page.</p>
    </main>
